10/10/2008
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- An explosion at a supermarket killed one person and injured three others Thursday (October 9th) in the central town of Vitez. 
One of the wounded is in serious condition. 
The incident happened at noon when shoppers found three explosive devices in the store, police spokesperson Ljubica Tomasevic said. 
Still unclear is whether the explosives were "planted or thrown", police said. 
(FoNet, RTRS, B92, Reuters - 09/10/08)
